A BANK MUST FREEZE funds in a delinquent taxpayer's account when the bank receives a levy notice from the Internal Revenue Service and wait 21 days before remitting the money to the IRS.
The procedure was described incorrectly in last Wednesday's Tax Report. 

(See: "Tax Report: A Special Summary and Forecast of Federal and State Tax Developments" -- WSJ Oct. 4, 1989) 

